+--------------------------------------------------------------------
+Mon May 20 10:00:00 UTC 2024 - pbuild-ai <pbuild-ai@suse.de>
+
+- Updated to version 5.4.0
+  * This release now uses Mike Haertel's MinRX regular expression matcher as the default regexp engine.
+  * New directive @nsinclude.
+  * length(array) is now a regular feature per 2024 POSIX standard.
+  * Hexadecimal floating-point values may now be used in program source code, with strtonum(), and with the -n/--non-decimal-data option.
+  * Support for UDP in gawk's networking support is now obsolete.
+  * Reading regular disk input files is faster.
+  * Removed a large number of small "replacement" files for standard functions.
+- Remove gawk-3.1.5.diff, multibyte.diff, fieldwidths.diff, embedded-nul.diff, parallel-make.diff, dfa-mbcset.diff, sub-common.diff, dev-fd.diff, numeric-conversion.diff (obsolete for version 5.4.0)
